   <mods:abstract>Attended Mr. Edgar's funeral at Pelham last Friday. Is attending the court
            of chancery in Albany; the population of that city seems to have almost entirely changed
            since John Jay left it. However, it is still the seat of political intrigue. Exertions
            are now underway to promote Mr. Crawford's election. It is said the canal will be
            completed next year and will be finished from Albany to Lockport this season. A boat
            from Lake Champlain has passed by Albany and has proceeded directly to New York; if such
            attempts succeed, the benefit derived by Albany from the canal will be much less than
            expected. The new Chancellor has given satisfaction to the bar thus far; Chancellor Kent
            is in Boston.</mods:abstract>
